modules.description: This module enables constructing OpenAPI-compliant web applications by defining routes with rich metadata, managing component references (schemas, responses, parameters), and configuring server settings. It provides HTTP method handlers, middleware integration, and execution pipelines to build and launch applications with typed routing and documented endpoints. Key use cases include generating OpenAPI specifications programmatically, defining RESTful APIs with typed requests/responses, and composing middleware-driven web services.

This module enables building OpenAPI-compliant web applications by defining typed routes with rich metadata, managing component references such as schemas and responses, and configuring server settings. It provides HTTP method handlers, middleware integration, and execution pipelines to construct and launch documented, type-safe APIs. You can generate OpenAPI specifications programmatically, define RESTful endpoints with typed requests and responses, and compose middleware-driven web services directly in OCaml.
